In case you missed it, here are the top Sport stories of the week: 1. HUNT OFF TO MAN CITY! Gavin Hunt will join English Premiership champions Manchester City for two weeks, as he studies their operations. 2. BREAKING: KOMPANY TABLES R20M OFFER FOR MOKOENA Belgium giants R.S.C Anderlecht, coached by Manchester City legend Vincent Kompany, have tabled an offer for Supersport United star midfielder Teboho Mokoena. 3. CHIEFS' 'OBRIGADO' RECOGNISED Kaizer Chiefs reserve team coach, Vela Khumalo, has confirmed to Sunsport that young sensation, Mfundo "Obrigado" Vilakazi will be part of Amakhosi's Diski Challenge team in the second round of the competition. 4. PSL ANNOUNCE LINE-UPS FOR COMPACT CUP The Premier Soccer League (PSL) has confirmed the starting line-ups for the DStv Compact Cup semi-final, which will be played next Saturday. 5. PIRATES' MHANGO COULD JUMP SHIP Orlando Pirates run the risk of losing striker Gabadinho Mhango who scored twice for his country Malawi when they beat Zimbabwe 2-0 in the Africa Cup of Nations (Afron) on Saturday, for free.